data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** The syntax is straightforward:

```csharp
Span<nint>  span  = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> uspan = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

On this 64-bit system, each element is 8 bytes (`sizeof(nint) == 8`). The only caveat is that `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context since `nint`/`nuint` don't have a compile-time-fixed size — but the `stackalloc` itself works in safe code just fine.
